oth an individual and a collective identity, as the people’s poet, a gay icon, and fabled member of a dead poets’ society. The specter of his violent death continues to haunt everything connected to Lorca, fueling the desire to fill in the gaps in the poet’s biography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311074977940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300265668?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300265668423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300265668/original  a978-3-11-073923-7  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074977-9  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099375-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DKUb2022  aZDB-23-UCY